Package: DistrictAssignments
Title: Geocode Member Lists and Assign Addresses to Districts
Version: 0.1.9
Authors@R:
    person("Abraham", "Ruiz", email = "abe@graycompass.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Converts addresses to coordinates (geocoding, via the ArcGIS
    World Geocoder) and assigns each address to the district(s) it falls
    within. Works with any number of district layers in a single run, so a
    member list can be geocoded once and joined against several districting
    files (congressional, state house, county, and so on). Includes a Shiny
    app ('run_app()') as a point-and-click interface over the same functions.
